div.p:
1. All your dute is:Ecclus 12.14. Phil. 4 17. 
               for he will bring every work to judgement with every ſecret thing whether good or evill. If a man doe but give an almes in uprightnes of heart, it will bee fruit which ſhall abound to his account. Then will be manifeſted in hearing: what you went forth to ſee, a man cloathed in ſoft rayment:
               Matth. 11.7.8. how many Sermons you have heard for no other end then children turne over bookes, to behold the gayes in them: when you went to heare men, and when to heare him that ſpeakes from heaven;Heb. 12.25. when you did in heating ſtoop to the Majeſty of God, and when to the authority of a man; when you did receive the truth only in the light, and when alſo in the love of it.
